        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 4:58PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 458 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 19
miles south of Ryegate, or 27 miles north of Columbus, moving east
at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail, along with
brief heavy rain and frequent lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Broadview, Halfbreed Lake Wildlife, Hailstone Wildlife Refuge,
Rapelje and Comanche.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
